UID:oWnoKSEAdHRbRcotzrJKd
SUMMARY:Distinguished Lecture with Francesco Bullo
DTSTAMP:20260626T013120Z
DTSTART:20261008T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP to Attend (https://k2i.wufoo.com/forms/distinguished-lectu
	re-with-francesco-bullo/): The distinguished lecture is from 4:00-5:00 PM\
	, followed by a social from 5:00-6:00 PMSpeaker: Professor Francesco Bullo
	 (https://fbullo.github.io/)— Professor of Mechanical Engineering at UC Sa
	nta Barbara  Talk Title:&#160\;TBD  When: Thursday\, October 8\, 2026 @ 4:
	00-6:00 PM Central  Where: Auditorium\, Duncan Hall\, Rice University (610
	0 Main St.\, Houston\, TX 77005)  Parking: Paid parking will be available 
	in Founder's Court Lot or the Entrance 3 (COB) Garage. Visit the Rice Univ
	ersity Campus Maps webpage (https://www.rice.edu/campus-maps) for directio
	ns.  Organizers: Ken Kennedy Institute (https://kenkennedy.rice.edu/)Speak
	er Bio        Francesco Bullo is Distinguished Professor and Mosher Endowe
	d Chair of Mechanical Engineering at the University of California\, Santa 
	Barbara\, CA\, USA. He received the Laurea degree in Electrical Engineerin
	g from the University of Padova\, Italy\, in 1994\, and the Ph.D. degree i
	n Control and Dynamical Systems from the California Institute of Technolog
	y\, Pasadena\, CA\, in 1998. His research interests include contraction th
	eory\, network systems\, neural networks\, and mathematical neuroscience. 
	He is the author or coauthor of Geometric Control of Mechanical Systems (S
	pringer\, 2004)\, Distributed Control of Robotic Networks (Princeton\, 200
	9)\, Lectures on Network Systems (KDP\, v1.7\, 2024)\, and Contraction The
	ory for Dynamical Systems (KDP\, v1.3 2026). He served as IEEE CSS Preside
	nt and SIAG CST Chair. He is a Fellow of ASME\, IEEE\, IFAC\, NetSci\, and
	 SIAM\n\nhttps://events.rice.edu/live/events/distinguished-lecture-with-fr
	ancesco-bullo\n\nFrom Rice University - Open to the Public
URL:https://events.rice.edu/live/events/distinguished-lecture-with-francesc
	o-bullo
GEO:29.7174;-95.4018
LOCATION:Duncan Hall
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rice-public-events
CATEGORIES:Rice University - Open to the Public
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
